Documents nearly 200 years of Central Florida history. Features a photo archives, of  more than 16,000 photographs and postcards, a research library, and a collection of archival material such as clipping files on thousands of subjects including local individuals and families, businesses, and significant events, Personal papers of notable individuals including civic and government leaders
Local history reference books;city directories; architectural and real estate resources; and genealogy resources and Central Florida maps from the 1840s to the present
